A Multiple Perceptron is an advanced type of ANN that contains:

Input Layer
One or more Hidden Layers
Output Layer

It is also called:

Multi Layer Perceptron (MLP)

==========

Structure of Multiple Perceptron
Input Layer
      ↓
Hidden Layer(s)
      ↓
Output Layer

========

Unlike Single Perceptron:

MLP has hidden layers
Can solve complex problems

========

Why Multiple Perceptron is Used?

Single perceptron can solve only simple linear problems.

MLP can solve:

Image recognition
Face detection
Speech recognition
Language translation

========



